---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteShell from "../components/SiteShell.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Sale — Tommy Day Art"
  description="Terms of sale for Tommy Day Art orders, preorders, artwork images, and checkout."
  canonicalUrl="/terms/"
>
  <SiteShell>
    <section class="page-intro-copy">
      <p class="section-eyebrow">Shop policies</p>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-serif">Terms of Sale</h1>
      <p>
        These terms cover purchases from Tommy Day Art. By placing an order, you agree to the order
        details shown at checkout and the policies linked from this site.
      </p>

      <h2>Artwork and product availability</h2>
      <p>
        Originals are one-of-one pieces. Prints, cards, and paper goods may be produced in small
        batches. Availability can change, and an order is not final until checkout is complete.
      </p>

      <h2>Preorders</h2>
      <p>
        Preorder items are paid for at checkout and produced after the preorder window closes.
        Estimated ship dates are good-faith estimates and may shift if production or packaging takes
        longer than expected.
      </p>

      <h2>Colors and images</h2>
      <p>
        Product photos are meant to represent the artwork as clearly as possible, but screen color,
        paper texture, and handmade materials can vary.
      </p>

      <h2>Copyright</h2>
      <p>
        Buying an original, print, card, or paper good does not transfer copyright or reproduction
        rights. Artwork images may not be reused commercially without written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Need help?</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hey@tommyday.com">hey@tommyday.com</a> with order questions or policy
        questions.
      </p>
    </section>
  </SiteShell>
</BaseLayout>
